WEBVTT

1
00:00:40.115 --> 00:00:42.845
(Jambi Studio)

2
00:00:51.924 --> 00:00:53.494
Just a second.

3
00:00:56.724 --> 00:00:59.395
How long do we need to do this? I'm getting cramps on my face.

4
00:01:00.234 --> 00:01:01.304
Don't look her way.

5
00:01:02.535 --> 00:01:04.135
The look in her eyes is telling me...

6
00:01:04.135 --> 00:01:05.704
that a crazy idea is forming inside her head.

7
00:01:05.704 --> 00:01:07.374
Acknowledge her now, and you'll be in trouble.

8
00:01:07.474 --> 00:01:09.675
Why? Why will we be in trouble?

9
00:01:10.075 --> 00:01:11.715
There's no safe zone around Jang Ha Ri.

10
00:01:14.885 --> 00:01:17.385
I didn't do anything wrong.

11
00:01:17.484 --> 00:01:18.755
I'm a bit scared.

12
00:01:20.285 --> 00:01:22.755
Since you think you're fine, why don't you deal with her?

13
00:01:25.594 --> 00:01:26.895
Is that really necessary?

14
00:01:28.895 --> 00:01:31.024
I should leave before she talks to me.

15
00:01:36.165 --> 00:01:39.404
Okay, we'll start shooting now.

16
00:01:39.805 --> 00:01:42.805
Loosen up. Bring your shoulders down.

17
00:01:42.805 --> 00:01:45.215
Put your chin down. Look into the camera lens.

18
00:01:45.514 --> 00:01:47.215
1, 2, 3. Let's see you smile.

19
00:01:47.215 --> 00:01:48.745
One more time.

20
00:01:49.445 --> 00:01:50.514
Yoon Jae Young.

21
00:01:50.844 --> 00:01:53.954
He may sound rough, but he has a nice personality.

22
00:01:54.154 --> 00:01:56.055
If my baby takes after him, it'll be smart.

23
00:01:58.355 --> 00:01:59.355
No.

24
00:01:59.355 --> 00:02:02.295
He's too much like a brother.

25
00:02:05.234 --> 00:02:06.295
Han I Sang.

26
00:02:06.795 --> 00:02:09.435
He seems to have a bad personality,

27
00:02:09.435 --> 00:02:11.374
but he's sometimes kind as well.

28
00:02:11.674 --> 00:02:14.204
I like his curiosity and how challenging he is.

29
00:02:15.344 --> 00:02:18.014
No, I won't be able to tell him.

30
00:02:20.374 --> 00:02:21.844
Choi Kang Eu Ddeum.

31
00:02:24.984 --> 00:02:25.984
What is his deal?

32
00:02:27.215 --> 00:02:28.685
- Great work. - You did great.

33
00:02:29.085 --> 00:02:31.495
- Good work. - Great work.

34
00:02:31.555 --> 00:02:33.355
- Thank you. - See you guys.

35
00:02:33.355 --> 00:02:34.394
What?

36
00:02:35.195 --> 00:02:36.264
You're going?

37
00:02:36.725 --> 00:02:37.764
She just left.

38
00:02:39.334 --> 00:02:41.304
- You did great. - You too.

39
00:02:44.065 --> 00:02:45.905
Where are you three going?

40
00:02:51.375 --> 00:02:54.045
I need to go home and take care of Do Ah.

41
00:02:54.045 --> 00:02:55.744
Your mom's probably having a hard time.

42
00:02:55.785 --> 00:02:58.184
I'm going to tell Mr. Kim that the shoot went well.

43
00:02:58.454 --> 00:03:01.524
I need to go to a shoot after lunch. Do you have something to say?

44
00:03:02.454 --> 00:03:04.755
Let me buy you lunch.

45
00:03:05.494 --> 00:03:07.725
That's great. You guys can eat together.

46
00:03:07.725 --> 00:03:08.795
- He's right. - Enjoy.

47
00:03:09.095 --> 00:03:10.095
Where are you going?

48
00:03:11.764 --> 00:03:13.494
My mom's free all afternoon.

49
00:03:14.864 --> 00:03:16.065
What's the matter with you?

50
00:03:16.304 --> 00:03:18.905
She can't watch Do Ah all day. She'll be exhausted.

51
00:03:19.005 --> 00:03:22.405
Then don't make her cook for you. Eat lunch with me.

52
00:03:23.174 --> 00:03:25.575
She's right. The three of you can chat...

53
00:03:25.575 --> 00:03:27.274
and have fun together.

54
00:03:27.274 --> 00:03:28.614
Eu Ddeum, you should come with us.

55
00:03:30.114 --> 00:03:32.614
Mr. Kim left to meet a client.

56
00:03:34.415 --> 00:03:36.255
He's probably back by now.

57
00:03:36.385 --> 00:03:38.325
This morning, I heard him say very loudly...

58
00:03:38.325 --> 00:03:40.125
that he has a lunch meeting with a client.

59
00:03:41.255 --> 00:03:42.295
- Eu Ddeum. - Yes?

60
00:03:42.295 --> 00:03:43.924
I have a lunch meeting with a client.

61
00:03:43.924 --> 00:03:44.994
I'll be back pretty late.

62
00:03:45.565 --> 00:03:46.764
Sorry. What?

63
00:03:49.464 --> 00:03:51.475
I'm going to be back...

64
00:03:51.804 --> 00:03:53.635
after lunch.

65
00:03:53.905 --> 00:03:55.545
I'm going to have lunch outside.

66
00:03:56.445 --> 00:03:57.475
I'll be back late.

67
00:04:01.274 --> 00:04:02.315
Let's go.

68
00:04:03.415 --> 00:04:04.415
Come on.

69
00:04:09.684 --> 00:04:12.095
Brace yourselves. We'll be okay.

70
00:04:21.505 --> 00:04:24.565
What's going on? Are you picking your future husband?

71
00:04:26.135 --> 00:04:27.575
Let me see.

72
00:04:28.244 --> 00:04:29.575
I choose...

73
00:04:30.445 --> 00:04:31.975
I'll send you a text.

74
00:04:32.445 --> 00:04:33.445
Good luck.

75
00:04:38.315 --> 00:04:39.815
Why isn't anyone sitting beside me?

76
00:04:40.214 --> 00:04:42.084
Right now, we're on the same side.

77
00:04:42.385 --> 00:04:45.025
Why did you suddenly want to eat with us?

78
00:04:45.624 --> 00:04:47.655
I just figured we should be friends.

79
00:04:48.265 --> 00:04:51.064
The three of you got to know each other,

80
00:04:51.064 --> 00:04:53.934
so I think we should take that friendship to another level.

81
00:04:55.804 --> 00:04:57.364
I guess we were scared for nothing.

82
00:04:57.665 --> 00:05:00.335
We became close because we were all scared of you.

83
00:05:00.434 --> 00:05:02.045
You're pretty fearless.

84
00:05:02.275 --> 00:05:04.275
It's because he's young. He doesn't know what's coming.

85
00:05:05.015 --> 00:05:06.015
Am I scary?

86
00:05:06.145 --> 00:05:09.345
Look in the mirror and see your eyes. They're very scary.

87
00:05:10.114 --> 00:05:11.215
Well...

88
00:05:11.684 --> 00:05:14.415
Now that I've aged, I realize that friends are precious.

89
00:05:14.684 --> 00:05:16.955
Let's get together often like this, get close,

90
00:05:16.955 --> 00:05:18.395
and check on each other's health status.

91
00:05:18.895 --> 00:05:22.494
- That being said, Eu Ddeum... - Yes?

92
00:05:22.725 --> 00:05:24.465
You seem quite healthy to me.

93
00:05:24.564 --> 00:05:26.234
Does it run in the family?

94
00:05:26.835 --> 00:05:29.765
I doubt your family has had any medical issues.

95
00:05:30.765 --> 00:05:32.374
No one in my family has been sick.

96
00:05:32.374 --> 00:05:33.574
I see.

97
00:05:34.674 --> 00:05:36.674
Meanwhile, my body isn't what it used to be.

98
00:05:36.674 --> 00:05:38.814
They say your body starts to power down...

99
00:05:38.814 --> 00:05:40.314
the moment you hit that 40 mark.

100
00:05:40.314 --> 00:05:44.114
That must be what's happening to me. I ache here and there. Right?

101
00:05:44.285 --> 00:05:45.785
That's not the case for me.

102
00:05:45.785 --> 00:05:47.554
- No underlying illnesses? - No.

103
00:05:47.984 --> 00:05:49.254
I see. That's good.

104
00:05:49.984 --> 00:05:53.694
We're at an age where health is a touchy subject for us.

105
00:05:54.324 --> 00:05:56.465
Hangovers aren't cured until the next evening...

106
00:05:56.465 --> 00:05:58.295
and it takes two days to recover from an all-nighter.

107
00:05:58.535 --> 00:06:00.095
So before we're hit with something bad,

108
00:06:00.194 --> 00:06:03.804
we should check our health at least twice a day.

109
00:06:04.465 --> 00:06:07.574
The doctor in me says that you have a liver problem.

110
00:06:08.004 --> 00:06:09.405
You can't have a part of mine though.

111
00:06:09.405 --> 00:06:10.874
It has hardened from all the liquor.

112
00:06:12.045 --> 00:06:13.114
You're out.

113
00:06:13.275 --> 00:06:14.415
Nice!

114
00:06:15.285 --> 00:06:17.585
You two seem like real siblings.

115
00:06:17.915 --> 00:06:19.054
How long have you been friends?

116
00:06:19.355 --> 00:06:20.915
Unfortunately, since in utero.

117
00:06:21.585 --> 00:06:22.725
Our moms were friends.

118
00:06:24.184 --> 00:06:26.754
No wonder you two are like elementary school kids.

119
00:06:27.295 --> 00:06:28.494
You're a polite one, aren't you?

120
00:06:29.194 --> 00:06:30.795
You just bad-mouthed us while holding a smile.

121
00:06:31.994 --> 00:06:33.965
I thought you were cousins.

122
00:06:34.494 --> 00:06:35.535
His aunt's daughter.

123
00:06:35.634 --> 00:06:36.934
You thought we were cousins?

124
00:06:37.364 --> 00:06:39.504
I'm her friend. Her boyfriend.

125
00:06:39.775 --> 00:06:41.905
Her boyfriend? Is he your boyfriend?

126
00:06:42.004 --> 00:06:44.374
No, a friend who's a boy. Don't mix those two up.

127
00:06:46.114 --> 00:06:48.345
Then why do you live together?

128
00:06:48.444 --> 00:06:51.585
- Well, he's putting us out... - Who says we can't?

129
00:06:55.424 --> 00:06:56.455
Especially when...

130
00:07:00.395 --> 00:07:01.795
we're this close?

131
00:07:04.064 --> 00:07:05.795
Yes, you're close enough to be smacked.

132
00:07:06.895 --> 00:07:07.895
Goodness.

133
00:07:08.705 --> 00:07:12.105
Anyway, it's nice to finally get to know you better.

134
00:07:12.475 --> 00:07:15.405
Let's keep this up and gradually get to know each other...

135
00:07:15.775 --> 00:07:16.944
even more.

136
00:07:17.174 --> 00:07:18.205
Sounds good.

137
00:07:18.314 --> 00:07:19.775
- Cheers. - Cheers.

138
00:07:19.775 --> 00:07:20.874
Cheers, everyone.

139
00:07:20.874 --> 00:07:23.515
All right. Here you go.

140
00:07:24.744 --> 00:07:30.184
(Episode 4: The Time One Needs to Understand Others)

141
00:07:32.725 --> 00:07:33.725
Stop right there.

142
00:07:40.395 --> 00:07:41.395
Follow me.

143
00:07:44.634 --> 00:07:45.705
Get back here!

144
00:07:47.074 --> 00:07:48.105
I'm sorry.

145
00:07:48.744 --> 00:07:50.174
I know it's something to be frowned upon.

146
00:07:50.174 --> 00:07:51.345
Didn't you know that?

147
00:07:51.645 --> 00:07:53.215
I didn't think I'd get caught.

148
00:07:54.074 --> 00:07:56.415
I understand how it can be frowned upon,

149
00:07:57.415 --> 00:08:01.285
but I don't think what I did was that wrong.

150
00:08:03.955 --> 00:08:07.194
Why should one's marital status make one's decision ethical?

151
00:08:07.295 --> 00:08:09.525
Am I supposed to engage in a debate?

152
00:08:10.194 --> 00:08:13.194
It's easy for everyone to accept how a married couple...

153
00:08:13.194 --> 00:08:14.665
would want a baby.

154
00:08:14.835 --> 00:08:17.734
What many can't accept is considered crazy.

155
00:08:18.705 --> 00:08:20.335
Am I a crazy cow then?

156
00:08:20.574 --> 00:08:21.744
Don't be too shocked by it.

157
00:08:21.944 --> 00:08:23.944
I never once thought you were in your right mind anyway.

158
00:08:24.345 --> 00:08:25.515
That's actually quite comforting.

159
00:08:31.415 --> 00:08:33.285
If you're going to set off a bomb,

160
00:08:33.754 --> 00:08:34.955
make sure the explosion's big.

161
00:08:42.924 --> 00:08:44.595
Are you siding with me?

162
00:08:45.335 --> 00:08:48.634
No. Let's just put it as me understanding how desperate you are.

163
00:08:49.105 --> 00:08:50.364
Just make sure you deal with the mess yourself.

164
00:08:52.074 --> 00:08:53.934
I doubt any harm was done.

165
00:08:54.775 --> 00:08:56.405
Only our people would recognize me anyway.

166
00:08:56.574 --> 00:08:58.915
Exactly. We all recognized you.

167
00:09:03.045 --> 00:09:04.885
- It's her, right? - Yes.

168
00:09:13.995 --> 00:09:15.865
So it's gossip over colleagues.

169
00:09:18.795 --> 00:09:19.865
Ha Ri.

170
00:09:23.834 --> 00:09:24.964
Please enjoy.

171
00:09:26.375 --> 00:09:27.434
Is it true?

172
00:09:28.704 --> 00:09:31.245
- What are people saying? - That it's not your first time...

173
00:09:32.074 --> 00:09:34.775
and that it's how you got pregnant with your first child.

174
00:09:34.875 --> 00:09:36.985
- Did I have a son or daughter? - Daughter.

175
00:09:36.985 --> 00:09:39.684
- Who does she take after? - She's a miniature version of you.

176
00:09:40.155 --> 00:09:41.214
Then she'll be cute.

177
00:09:41.214 --> 00:09:43.785
Hold on. That I didn't hear.

178
00:09:45.094 --> 00:09:47.854
Anyway, I hope that this unknown child of mine...

179
00:09:47.854 --> 00:09:50.224
lives a great life without her mother.

180
00:09:52.365 --> 00:09:54.334
You're going to let people say...

181
00:09:54.334 --> 00:09:56.304
that you abandoned your child?

182
00:09:57.704 --> 00:10:01.304
I can't believe she isn't taking this seriously.

183
00:10:02.574 --> 00:10:03.574
Gosh.

184
00:10:11.854 --> 00:10:13.015
If I don't get married?

185
00:10:14.084 --> 00:10:15.354
If you're gone?

186
00:10:16.354 --> 00:10:18.084
Should I live just for myself?

187
00:10:18.995 --> 00:10:20.655
You say you live for me.

188
00:10:22.064 --> 00:10:23.625
Should I live alone without any family,

189
00:10:24.064 --> 00:10:27.365
living just for myself, and then die alone?

190
00:10:31.334 --> 00:10:32.704
But you'll be too lonely.

191
00:10:35.245 --> 00:10:36.875
When you're old, everything is upsetting.

192
00:10:39.745 --> 00:10:41.015
If you have no one,

193
00:10:43.115 --> 00:10:44.844
who will take care of you when you're sick?

194
00:10:58.094 --> 00:11:00.094
Auntie, are you drinking?

195
00:11:00.995 --> 00:11:03.204
- You shouldn't. - Shut it...

196
00:11:03.635 --> 00:11:04.704
and get over here.

197
00:11:09.005 --> 00:11:10.104
Jae Young.

198
00:11:11.704 --> 00:11:13.375
What do you think of Ha Ri?

199
00:11:16.184 --> 00:11:18.755
Mom. Can I call you that instead of Auntie?

200
00:11:19.054 --> 00:11:20.985
You seem more like my mom these days.

201
00:11:23.285 --> 00:11:24.684
What are you getting at?

202
00:11:24.684 --> 00:11:26.354
Ha Ri and I have been friends since birth.

203
00:11:26.795 --> 00:11:28.054
We're already family.

204
00:11:28.155 --> 00:11:30.324
And all I want to do is make it official on paper.

205
00:11:30.924 --> 00:11:32.964
Why won't you see Ha Ri as a woman?

206
00:11:33.194 --> 00:11:35.365
She's pretty, kind, humorous,

207
00:11:35.665 --> 00:11:37.064
and charming.

208
00:11:37.505 --> 00:11:38.804
It's hard not to be attracted to her.

209
00:11:39.505 --> 00:11:40.604
I know.

210
00:11:42.704 --> 00:11:44.745
Of course I'm aware that Ha Ri's a catch.

211
00:11:45.674 --> 00:11:47.045
It's why I'm not the man for her.

212
00:11:50.145 --> 00:11:51.214
Come on.

213
00:11:51.814 --> 00:11:55.354
Why would you want her to be with a single father?

214
00:11:56.255 --> 00:11:58.084
She should marry someone...

215
00:11:59.724 --> 00:12:01.554
who is better than me.

216
00:12:03.824 --> 00:12:04.995
Of course she should.

217
00:12:23.584 --> 00:12:24.714
Darn, it hurts.

218
00:12:24.714 --> 00:12:25.854
My gosh!

219
00:12:30.584 --> 00:12:31.995
It hurts.

220
00:12:38.694 --> 00:12:39.795
Seriously?

221
00:12:47.775 --> 00:12:48.844
Here.

222
00:12:49.405 --> 00:12:50.444
Let's go.

223
00:12:52.015 --> 00:12:53.015
We live together.

224
00:12:55.714 --> 00:12:58.115
Then why do you live together?

225
00:12:58.115 --> 00:13:01.354
- Well, he's putting us out... - Who says we can't?

226
00:13:04.224 --> 00:13:05.324
Especially when...

227
00:13:07.554 --> 00:13:08.824
we're this close?

228
00:13:18.635 --> 00:13:21.334
How does this make any sense?

229
00:13:21.635 --> 00:13:24.245
A man and a woman who has a close relationship...

230
00:13:24.604 --> 00:13:26.574
are living in the same house?

231
00:13:26.674 --> 00:13:27.674
Answer me.

232
00:13:28.474 --> 00:13:30.515
Why won't you say anything?

233
00:13:31.245 --> 00:13:32.554
Whatever. Forget about it.

234
00:13:33.485 --> 00:13:34.485
Unbelievable.

235
00:13:45.265 --> 00:13:47.535
You prepared a feast.

236
00:13:48.464 --> 00:13:49.735
Anyway, thank you.

237
00:13:53.174 --> 00:13:54.735
Everything smells nice.

238
00:13:58.145 --> 00:13:59.974
- Do you want soup? - Yes.

239
00:14:07.615 --> 00:14:08.824
Gosh, it looks delicious.

240
00:14:08.824 --> 00:14:10.184
It sure does.

241
00:14:14.094 --> 00:14:17.265
I'm not saying that I won't ever get married.

242
00:14:18.424 --> 00:14:21.135
But realistically speaking, it's too hard to find anyone.

243
00:14:21.135 --> 00:14:23.665
There aren't any decent guys around me.

244
00:14:24.334 --> 00:14:27.604
I'm at an age where pregnancy is more urgent...

245
00:14:32.745 --> 00:14:35.015
Mom, I...

246
00:14:38.245 --> 00:14:40.255
Just how dense are you?

247
00:14:48.724 --> 00:14:50.025
Come on.

248
00:14:50.025 --> 00:14:51.594
Just how dense are you?

249
00:14:52.035 --> 00:14:54.194
Grandma's already upset as it is.

250
00:14:54.295 --> 00:14:57.635
What are you doing by adding fuel to the flame?

251
00:14:59.804 --> 00:15:01.834
Use your common sense, Mom.

252
00:15:04.174 --> 00:15:05.344
There's no way I'd choose you.

253
00:15:06.415 --> 00:15:09.184
- What do you mean? - Nothing.

254
00:15:10.944 --> 00:15:11.985
What did you just mean?

255
00:15:12.184 --> 00:15:13.354
Just get back to your meal.

256
00:15:13.655 --> 00:15:14.684
I should eat.

257
00:15:35.875 --> 00:15:37.005
(Jambi Studio)

258
00:15:37.005 --> 00:15:38.915
Please put the kids in front.

259
00:15:38.915 --> 00:15:40.645
- Gather round. - Okay.

260
00:15:40.844 --> 00:15:42.444
- Look here, kids. - Look here.

261
00:15:42.444 --> 00:15:44.745
- Look here. Okay. - Right here.

262
00:15:44.745 --> 00:15:45.915
How cute.

263
00:15:46.285 --> 00:15:47.915
Where did you find them?

264
00:15:48.054 --> 00:15:49.625
They look just like each other.

265
00:15:50.054 --> 00:15:52.694
With a little creative liberty, they're the genius father and son,

266
00:15:52.954 --> 00:15:54.824
athletic father and son, and artistic mother and daughter.

267
00:16:02.204 --> 00:16:03.704
He looks normal enough.

268
00:16:06.474 --> 00:16:07.604
He's handsome.

269
00:16:08.275 --> 00:16:10.505
He has a sharp nose and nice jawline.

270
00:16:10.704 --> 00:16:11.844
And fair skin.

