00:51:03.647 --> 00:51:05.546
Why are you making me a bad daughter?

807
00:51:06.446 --> 00:51:07.857
Did someone say you were bad?

808
00:51:08.156 --> 00:51:11.587
Everyone knows you work long hours and can't even come home.

809
00:51:13.057 --> 00:51:15.357
Don't mind me, and focus on your job.

810
00:51:15.357 --> 00:51:17.397
How can I not mind you when you're sick?

811
00:51:17.397 --> 00:51:20.026
I'm not sick. They said I'm fine.

812
00:51:20.397 --> 00:51:23.267
You should eat and sleep properly as you work.

813
00:51:25.937 --> 00:51:30.337
I... I'm always making you worry about me.

814
00:51:34.317 --> 00:51:35.946
Can't I worry about you too?

815
00:51:41.057 --> 00:51:44.127
Even if I act immature,

816
00:51:44.457 --> 00:51:48.026
I can take care of you, so have faith in your daughter.

817
00:51:52.267 --> 00:51:55.537
Why would you take care of me? I'm not terminally ill.

818
00:51:56.767 --> 00:51:59.466
Save your nagging for your kids.

819
00:51:59.866 --> 00:52:02.776
Get sperm or whatever. Have kids using whatever means you want.

820
00:52:02.776 --> 00:52:04.006
It's so annoying.

821
00:52:06.406 --> 00:52:07.647
No, that's...

822
00:52:16.057 --> 00:52:18.256
I thought I could raise a baby well,

823
00:52:20.926 --> 00:52:23.426
but I didn't think about the child who'd have to live without a dad.

824
00:52:28.567 --> 00:52:29.767
I was being greedy.

825
00:52:34.477 --> 00:52:35.636
I mean,

826
00:52:36.307 --> 00:52:39.006
I was fine although I only had you, so...

827
00:52:47.386 --> 00:52:49.317
I thought I could do well.

828
00:52:52.057 --> 00:52:53.787
But I should've thought about the kid first.

829
00:52:57.596 --> 00:52:59.127
I don't think I'm qualified.

830
00:53:04.667 --> 00:53:05.966
Did someone say something?

831
00:53:06.267 --> 00:53:07.366
No.

832
00:53:09.906 --> 00:53:10.946
My gosh.

833
00:53:11.607 --> 00:53:14.076
Parents have kids because they want to.

834
00:53:15.247 --> 00:53:18.346
No baby is born out of their own will.

835
00:53:18.346 --> 00:53:22.087
Do you think I gave birth to you because you begged me to?

836
00:53:22.287 --> 00:53:24.156
What kind of nonsense are you talking about?

837
00:53:26.727 --> 00:53:28.857
You don't study and take tests to become a mother.

838
00:53:28.857 --> 00:53:30.826
You become a mother after you give birth.

839
00:53:31.497 --> 00:53:34.196
There's no license for that. Don't say you're not qualified.

840
00:53:35.997 --> 00:53:37.636
You're right. There's no license.

841
00:53:38.837 --> 00:53:41.906
But if there was a license test for that,

842
00:53:42.076 --> 00:53:43.076
you'd get the highest score.

843
00:53:43.076 --> 00:53:45.906
So be good to your mom.

844
00:53:46.207 --> 00:53:48.377
Anyway, I don't think this was a fight.

845
00:53:48.377 --> 00:53:51.846
It was really nice to watch you guys reconcile and make peace.

846
00:53:51.986 --> 00:53:55.216
Do Ah is crying. I'll leave you guys to wrap it up. I love you guys.

847
00:53:55.656 --> 00:53:56.756
Do Ah.

848
00:53:58.386 --> 00:54:00.026
What was that? My gosh.

849
00:54:31.986 --> 00:54:34.426
Aren't you going to drink? Let's have a drink.

850
00:54:34.727 --> 00:54:36.957
No, I don't want to become an alcoholic like you.

851
00:54:36.957 --> 00:54:38.426
I'll sue you for slander.

852
00:54:38.627 --> 00:54:39.727
Don't do that.

853
00:54:40.627 --> 00:54:42.397
I'm sick of getting punished.

854
00:54:43.667 --> 00:54:45.107
Are you serious?

855
00:54:46.537 --> 00:54:47.776
What can you do?

856
00:54:47.877 --> 00:54:49.576
You're just going through...

857
00:54:49.937 --> 00:54:52.107
the adversities and hardships of becoming a mom.

858
00:54:55.776 --> 00:54:58.346
Come to think of it, even you didn't ask.

859
00:54:59.486 --> 00:55:00.486
What?

860
00:55:01.017 --> 00:55:04.557
No one asked me why, but I Sang did.

861
00:55:07.557 --> 00:55:09.426
He asked me why I want to become a mom.

862
00:55:12.466 --> 00:55:14.736
What other reason could there be?

863
00:55:15.596 --> 00:55:17.667
You want to become a mom because of your motherly instincts.

864
00:55:18.307 --> 00:55:21.837
Yes, you're right.

865
00:55:24.707 --> 00:55:28.647
But on my way home, I suddenly remembered...

866
00:55:30.647 --> 00:55:32.486
my elementary school graduation day.

867
00:55:36.886 --> 00:55:39.057
Don't be a scrooge and just get her a big bouquet.

868
00:55:39.156 --> 00:55:40.526
And take a lot of photos.

869
00:55:45.926 --> 00:55:48.366
Don't go anywhere else, okay? If you do, I'll get really angry.

870
00:55:48.997 --> 00:55:50.267
Okay.

871
00:55:58.247 --> 00:56:01.046
Dad, get me a big bouquet of roses.

872
00:56:01.216 --> 00:56:02.276
Okay.

873
00:56:06.546 --> 00:56:09.017
Ha Ri, I need to get a film...

874
00:56:09.017 --> 00:56:11.227
for the camera.

875
00:56:11.227 --> 00:56:12.287
You should go without me.

876
00:56:12.886 --> 00:56:14.957
- Do you know which class I'm in? - What?

877
00:56:15.326 --> 00:56:17.526
I'm in class 6-5. It's on the 4th floor.

878
00:56:18.096 --> 00:56:19.426
Can you find your way there?

879
00:56:19.796 --> 00:56:20.826
Of course.

880
00:56:21.397 --> 00:56:23.366
You go first. I'll be right there.

881
00:56:28.576 --> 00:56:29.707
Wait for me!

882
00:56:40.946 --> 00:56:44.357
(Ssanggang Elementary School, 23rd Graduation Ceremony)

883
00:56:44.357 --> 00:56:46.787
(Congratulations on your graduation)

884
00:56:46.787 --> 00:56:48.296
No matter how long I waited,

885
00:56:49.926 --> 00:56:51.497
my dad didn't show up.

886
00:56:52.466 --> 00:56:54.267
I was the only one standing there all by myself,

887
00:56:55.067 --> 00:56:58.207
and I was embarrassed because it felt like all eyes were on me.

888
00:57:00.067 --> 00:57:02.006
But I couldn't go home.

889
00:57:04.846 --> 00:57:07.977
Because I knew my dad won't ever come back.

890
00:57:12.087 --> 00:57:14.917
Ha Ri, what are you doing here?

891
00:57:15.156 --> 00:57:16.256
Where is your dad?

892
00:57:17.357 --> 00:57:18.386
I don't know.

893
00:57:25.426 --> 00:57:28.167
Ha Ri, let's take a photo together. Come here.

894
00:57:30.096 --> 00:57:31.207
Why?

895
00:57:31.207 --> 00:57:32.567
- Stand there. - You guys are friends.

896
00:57:33.167 --> 00:57:34.707
Smile.

897
00:57:34.776 --> 00:57:36.576
- 1, 2, 3. - 1, 2, 3.

898
00:57:38.276 --> 00:57:40.807
Let's take one more photo. Give me a bright smile.

899
00:57:40.807 --> 00:57:43.076
You look really ugly right now.

900
00:57:43.477 --> 00:57:44.486
Why you...

901
00:57:45.886 --> 00:57:47.817
- Oh, gosh! - No, wait!

902
00:57:48.216 --> 00:57:49.386
Ha Ri, stop.

903
00:57:49.386 --> 00:57:52.057
- What's the matter? - Stop it.

904
00:57:52.057 --> 00:57:53.857
- Stop it, Jae Young. - Ha Ri.

905
00:57:53.886 --> 00:57:56.397
My goodness, what did you say?

906
00:57:56.397 --> 00:57:58.026
Jae Young, stop it.

907
00:58:01.796 --> 00:58:04.537
(Pig Skin)

908
00:58:07.837 --> 00:58:09.576
- Mom. - Oh, dear.

909
00:58:11.276 --> 00:58:12.307
Ha Ri, what's wrong?

910
00:58:12.906 --> 00:58:14.616
Mom!

911
00:58:14.716 --> 00:58:15.716
Where's your dad?

912
00:58:23.187 --> 00:58:24.216
Is it yummy?

913
00:58:24.986 --> 00:58:26.026
Yes.

914
00:58:28.826 --> 00:58:30.426
It's all over your mouth.

915
00:58:35.067 --> 00:58:36.466
You're okay without your dad, right?

916
00:58:41.906 --> 00:58:42.977
Yes.

917
00:58:45.946 --> 00:58:46.977
Eat some meat.

918
00:58:54.116 --> 00:58:56.486
That's when I promised myself to become an awesome person...

919
00:58:57.087 --> 00:58:58.656
when I grow up.

920
00:58:59.557 --> 00:59:01.397
What kind of an awesome person?

921
00:59:03.256 --> 00:59:04.296
A mom.

922
00:59:10.167 --> 00:59:12.937
My mom is the most awesome person in the world.

923
00:59:20.247 --> 00:59:21.346
A mother.

924
01:00:09.426 --> 01:00:11.627
They'll probably cut her wage for about 1 to 3 months.

925
01:00:13.727 --> 01:00:14.866
Do you think this is fun?

926
01:00:15.897 --> 01:00:17.136
No, I'm worried.

927
01:00:17.437 --> 01:00:20.906
The worst thing that can happen to an employee is not getting paid.

928
01:00:21.807 --> 01:00:24.377
Did she really make such a big mistake?

929
01:00:25.546 --> 01:00:28.377
She tarnished the company's reputation and credibility.

930
01:00:30.377 --> 01:00:33.317
I should've just quietly dealt with those mothers.

931
01:00:41.357 --> 01:00:42.357
What happened?

932
01:00:44.826 --> 01:00:46.167
They suspended her for a month.

933
01:00:46.466 --> 01:00:47.497
- What? - What?

934
01:00:48.667 --> 01:00:51.296
Then she won't get paid for a month?

935
01:00:51.406 --> 01:00:53.267
This is unbelievable.

936
01:00:53.267 --> 01:00:55.037
They can't suspend her for this.

937
01:00:55.307 --> 01:00:57.307
How are we going to meet the deadline for our project?

938
01:00:58.006 --> 01:00:59.207
Where is Ha Ri?

939
01:01:01.817 --> 01:01:03.017
Hey, Ha Ri.

940
01:01:05.017 --> 01:01:06.687
I heard what happened.

941
01:01:07.346 --> 01:01:10.787
Hey... Ha Ri, I'll... I'll see you.

942
01:01:14.587 --> 01:01:17.457
She got suspended for a month.

943
01:01:18.296 --> 01:01:19.897
She looks really angry, doesn't she?

944
01:01:45.756 --> 01:01:47.227
This game is for two people. You can't play it by yourself.

945
01:01:56.196 --> 01:01:57.736
Let's do this.

946
01:02:03.377 --> 01:02:04.537
Over there.

947
01:02:05.607 --> 01:02:07.076
To your left!

948
01:02:07.747 --> 01:02:09.247
This is hard.

949
01:02:09.247 --> 01:02:10.517
Shoot!

950
01:02:10.517 --> 01:02:12.687
You were supposed to shoot that.

951
01:02:13.346 --> 01:02:14.346
My gosh, no!

952
01:02:17.986 --> 01:02:19.026
(You Lose)

953
01:02:23.357 --> 01:02:25.497
You acted like a natural, so I thought you'd be a sniper.

954
01:02:27.196 --> 01:02:28.236
What next?

955
01:02:30.037 --> 01:02:32.906
Should we drink or go to the beach?

956
01:02:36.136 --> 01:02:38.247
I'm no longer stressed.

957
01:02:39.006 --> 01:02:40.276
I may have gotten suspended,

958
01:02:41.076 --> 01:02:42.247
but I still need to meet a deadline.

959
01:02:52.957 --> 01:02:54.926
This is fun, right?

960
01:02:55.326 --> 01:02:57.656
Let me see you smile!

961
01:02:57.926 --> 01:02:59.667
Over here! Look!

962
01:02:59.926 --> 01:03:01.696
Give me a smile.

963
01:03:01.966 --> 01:03:04.096
Smile, Yu Bin. Look here, Yu Bin.

964
01:03:04.236 --> 01:03:05.307
Over here!

965
01:03:06.307 --> 01:03:07.807
Yu Bin, give me a smile! He's laughing too!

966
01:03:07.807 --> 01:03:09.636
Look! He's laughing too!

967
01:03:16.216 --> 01:03:18.017
Yes, let's laugh!

968
01:03:20.817 --> 01:03:23.256
There you go. All right.

969
01:03:25.687 --> 01:03:27.656
I need him to cry this time.

970
01:03:28.796 --> 01:03:29.857
What do I do?

971
01:03:30.857 --> 01:03:33.497
Yoo Bin, roar.

972
01:03:33.796 --> 01:03:35.497
Roar! I'm coming to get you.

973
01:03:37.196 --> 01:03:38.767
He is a very bad man.

974
01:03:38.837 --> 01:03:40.837
Look at me hit the bad man.

975
01:03:40.837 --> 01:03:42.136
How nasty!

976
01:03:44.676 --> 01:03:45.846
You naughty boy.

977
01:03:51.346 --> 01:03:52.417
You naughty boy!

978
01:03:58.426 --> 01:04:00.057
As if you stood a chance.

979
01:04:00.256 --> 01:04:01.526
That's what I call talent.

980
01:04:08.366 --> 01:04:10.537
- Can you check the photos? - Sure.

981
01:04:15.307 --> 01:04:16.576
Let's see.

982
01:04:19.147 --> 01:04:20.776
That one.

983
01:04:23.576 --> 01:04:24.846
They're all good.

984
01:04:25.046 --> 01:04:26.287
This should be the main photo.

985
01:04:27.216 --> 01:04:29.417
Mr. Han,

986
01:04:30.587 --> 01:04:31.727
I'm impressed.

987
01:04:39.826 --> 01:04:42.696
(Good job!)

988
01:04:46.667 --> 01:04:49.707
It's us grown-ups who really need compliments.

989
01:04:54.107 --> 01:04:55.346
Good job, Mr. Han.

990
01:04:56.747 --> 01:04:59.787
- Ha Ri, the baby's mom is leaving. - Okay.

991
01:05:01.346 --> 01:05:02.357
Goodbye.

992
01:05:02.357 --> 01:05:09.156
(Good job!)

993
01:05:44.727 --> 01:05:45.897
This is bad.

994
01:05:49.497 --> 01:05:54.866
(Good job!)

995
01:06:21.096 --> 01:06:23.667
(We thank Jang Gwang for his cameo appearance.)

996
01:06:42.017 --> 01:06:44.786
(Oh My Baby)

997
01:06:44.786 --> 01:06:46.327
You two were married?

998
01:06:46.687 --> 01:06:47.827
A second marriage?

999
01:06:47.827 --> 01:06:49.596
Right, the sperm donation.

1000
01:06:49.926 --> 01:06:53.067
I wouldn't have to be a father to your baby,

1001
01:06:53.426 --> 01:06:55.397
- so I'll do you a favor. - Really?

1002
01:06:55.397 --> 01:06:56.697
She's staying the night out?

1003
01:06:56.697 --> 01:06:58.166
Isn't she alone with Mr. Han?

1004
01:06:58.767 --> 01:07:02.636
You found the one place that only has one inn.

1005
01:07:02.636 --> 01:07:04.937
She'll get an earful from me once she gets back.

1006
01:07:05.046 --> 01:07:07.807
Is he the one that I shouldn't have let go of?

1007
01:07:08.147 --> 01:07:09.376
How should...

1008
01:07:11.477 --> 01:07:12.886
we spend the night?

